HEADWORD: Spindling
<hw>Spin"dling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Long and slender,
or disproportionately tall and slender; <as>as, a <ex>spindling</ex>
tree; a <ex>spindling</ex> boy.</as></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> spindly.</syn>
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spindly</ent>⟦br⟧
